      <h4>Goal</h4>
      <p>The game is won by successfully maneuvering a red <span class="small-peg r"></span> or green <span class="small-peg g"></span> peg next to the other peg of the same color.</p>
      <h4>Overview</h4>
      <p>Pegger is a peg jumping strategy game for two players. On your turn, select a red <span class="small-peg r"></span>, green <span class="small-peg g"></span>, or yellow <span class="small-peg y"></span> peg and then select the hole <span class="small-peg"></span> where you would like to move the peg.</p>
      <p>Players take turns moving pegs until either both red pegs or both green pegs are next to each other. Sorry, diagonals and yellow pegs don't count and you can't undo the previous turn!</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-lg-6">
      <h4>Rules</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>A peg must be moved into an adjacent hole or jump an adjacent peg into a hole.</li>
        <li>Diagonal movement is not permitted.</li>
        <li>Only red <span class="small-peg r"></span> and green <span class="small-peg g"></span> pegs count toward victory.</li>
        <li>Yellow <span class="small-peg y"></span> pegs may be moved but are considered neutral and do not count toward victory.</li>
        <li>A player may not undo the most recent completed turn.</li>
      </ul>
